t.\n\n- Darynda Jones, Third Grave Dead Ahead\n|\nSuccess or failure is not a one day event, but continuous life process. Each day you succeed and each day you fail with life, and most of the time, success follows the failure.\n\n- Roshan\n|\nTo understand life is to understand ourselves, and that is both the beginning and the end of education.\n\n- Jiddu Krishnamurti, Education and the Significance of Life\n|\nThine are these orbs of light and shade;Thou madest Life in man and brute;Thou madest Death; and lo, thy footIs on the skull which thou hast made.\n\n- Alfred Tennyson, In Memoriam, Maud and Other Poems\n|\nWith every breath you take, someone just took their last. Stop complaining about life. It has given you much more than what you appreciate.\n\n- Manoj Arora, Dream On: Every setback is a little nudge from HIM to Dream On\n|\nShe has learned to love. To fear. To hate. And then to love again. Through it all, she writes.” ~Once Upon A Time There Was A Girl\n\n- Kimberly Kinrade, Bits of You & Pieces of Me\n|\nCreate an environment that is conducive to your emotional and personal growth. Surround yourself with caring and positive people who support you, and reflect who you want to be.\n\n- Steve\n|\nI lean to you, numb as a fossil. Tell me I'm here.\n\n- Sylvia Plath, The Collected Poems\n|\nIt has been said, 'the truth will make men free.' The truth alone has never made anyone free. It is only doubt which will bring mental emancipation.\n\n- Anton\n|\nThe idea that I could work wonders as the Lord flutters through my mind like a glamorous butterfly. I hasten to catch it, but it escapes into the depths of my mind.\n\n- Stefan Emunds, The Priest Whisperer\n|\nTo take a leap, you must hope not to fall.\n\n- Myles\n|\nL'artGreen arsenic smeared on an egg-white cloth, Crushed strawberries! Come, let us feast our eyes.\n\n- Ezra\n|\nPoetry, is a life long war wagedagainst ineffable beauty.\n\n- Atticus Poetry, Love Her Wild: Poems\n|\nRespecting requests, rules and privacy is a universal law. You break that basic etiquette 101, you're seriously flawed.\n\n- Hlovate, Contengan Jalanan\n|\nThink 'Energy' before opening your mouth. Send out good vibes in every word you pronounce.\n\n- Diana Dentinger, Modus Vivendi: Your Life Your Way\n|\nYou are perfect, not tomorrow, not in the future, but today.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nAs we expand our knowledge of good books, we shrink the circle of men whose company we appreciate.\n\n- Ludwig\n|\nIf fiction and fantasy books are escapism, then let an author write them so as to better equip the reader to face reality by the end.\n\n- Brett\n|\nBooks and doors are the same thing. You open them, and you go through into another world.\n\n- Jeanette\n|\nPlanning your life creates within you a feeling of control which produces self-confidence, self-responsibility and self-assurance.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nDo not be discourage by the height of the mountain, one step at a time will lead you there; and now is the time to begin tomorrow may be too late.\n\n- ANIKOR\n|\nLike water leaking through a dam,' said Piper.'Yeah,' smiled Percy. 'We've got a dam hole.''What?' Piper asked.'Nothing,' he said. 'Inside joke.\n\n- Rick Riordan, The Mark of Athena\n|\nI wondered if the person who really loves you is the person who knows all your stories, the person who WANTS to know all your stories.\n\n- Gabrielle Zevin, Memoirs of a Teenage Amnesiac\n|\nthe important thing is not what we (look) like,but the role we play in our best friend's life.\n\n- Cecelia Ahern, If You Could See Me Now\n|\nIf you try to do a task at your odd hours, you will waste so much time only to find out that you did a poor job after all.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nOur power lies in our small daily choices, one after another, to create eternal ripples of a life well lived.\n\n- Mollie\n|\nWe grow not through the words we read or the lessons we see, but through the love we feel & and the paths we lead.\n\n- Robert\n|\nYou just don't know writers. They'll use anything, anybody. They'll eat their young.\n\n- Dennis Potter, The Singing Detective\n|\nThe few Americans he had encountered in his lifetime had all seemed flat to him, as if freedom weakened one's capacity for intense emotion by demanding too little of it.\n\n- G. Willow Wilson, Alif the Unseen\n|\nChildren pay little attention to their parents' teachings, but reproduce their characters faithfully\n\n- Mason\n|\nLife teaches us many lessons daily, even from our mishaps, only if we pay attention\n\n- Bernard\n|\nShe's an array of undiscovered words, of feeling beyond my threshold. I'm just a man, trying to hold himself together in her wake.\n\n- Hubert\n|\nIt is always useful to face an enemy who is prepared to die for his country,' he read. 'This means that both you and he have exactly the same aim in mind.\n\n- Terry Pratchett, Jingo\n|\nRegardless of one’s age, acquiring new knowledge has always been useful.\n\n- Eraldo\n|\nTrue religion should be able to respond to the dark melodies, the faulty and hideous sounds that echo from the heart of men.\n\n- Shūsaku Endō, Scandal\n|\nPleasure awakens the body, wisdom awakens the mind, joy awakens the heart, and love awakens the soul.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nMany things that don't really mean so much of anything, are wonderful.\n\n- C.\n|\nYou have tasted of death now,” said the old man. “Is it good?” “It is good,” said Mossy. “It is better than life.”“No,” said the old man: “it is only more life.\n\n- George MacDonald, The Golden Key\n|\nMen can dig wells, but they can’t create water.\n\n- Craig\n|\nDo all you have agreed to do, and do not encroach on other persons or their property.\n\n- Richard J. Maybury, Whatever Happened to Justice? Revised Edition\n|\nI would rather live 10 years doing what I Love, than drag through Life 50 years, hating everyday I Live.\n\n- RVM\n|\nThe ultimate philosophy of life is not found in words, but it is found in the ways of living life.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nYou can be great in any area of life, just learn to convert time into added value and tangible products.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nWe’re organisms; we’re conceived, we’re born, we live, we die, and we decay. But as we decay we feed the world of the living: plants and bugs and bacteria.\n\n- William M. Bass, Death's Acre: Inside the Legendary Forensic Lab the Body Farm Where the Dead Do Tell Tales\n|\nFirst, know where you want to go. Then, go where you want to go. You are your own pilot and you can choose your Destination.\n\n- RVM\n|\nA relationship is likely to last way longer, if each partner convinces or has convinced themselves that they do not deserve their partner, even if that is not true.\n\n- Mokokoma\n|\nThe mind shrinks or expands in proportion to one’s wisdom; the heart, in proportion to one’s courage; and the soul, in proportion to one’s love.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nTo become a better you, hurry up and take risks.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Become a Better You\n|\nHappiness is a gift which is priceless,You can only receive itif you can give it....\n\n- Adil\n|\nWhere even ravi (the sun) cannot reach, there will go a kavi (poet).' - Vimalananda\n\n- Robert E. Svoboda, Aghora II: Kundalini\n|\nThe bittersweet about truth is that nothing could be more hurtful, yet nothing could be more helpful.\n\n- Mike  Norton, Just Another War Story\n|\nThe definition of freedom is that there is no dependency. Despite having the physical body, one feels no dependency.\n\n- Dada\n|\nYoung love is so ridiculous, as is middle-aged and old love. And it’s also hilarious. When have you ever felt so vulnerable and wonderful and terrible at the same time?\n\n- Grace\n|\nYour anger towards ungodliness, towards injustice and the likes, will create a hunger in you to fulfill a particular purpose meant for you.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nInstead of worrying about what you cannot control, focus your energy on what you can create.\n\n- Roy\n|\nMarty, my mother used to say 'Never get greedy with God.' I think what she meant was 'Don't dare ask for more if you already have what you need.'\n\n- James Patterson, The Christmas Wedding\n|\nYou don’t choose your purpose, you simply discover it.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nbecause God has spoken, and everything else is commentary.\n\n- Rob Bell, Velvet Elvis: Repainting the Christian Faith\n|\nWhat would it be like if I were free, not enslaved by my conditioning?\n\n- Aldous Huxley, Brave New World"